				The value of ANY item is ONLY what someone is willing to PAY for it...<BR>
As such, I was offering 1250pp, a BIBS, a Barbed Whip, Crafted legs and gloves, and a Chitin Shell Tunic on the Innoruuk server...<BR>
Total combined value: A LOT...<BR>
That STILL didn't keep people from LOSING THEIR MINDS about value....<BR>
One person wanted a FULL SET of Crafted for a DR...  yet ANOTHER wanted a Manastone...   (!!!) <BR>
Their excuses for NOT accepting my offer was that they were TOO LAZY to try to sell off the items I was offering in the deal... but DAMNED if they weren't putting one HELL of a lot of effort into getting their demands met...<BR>
Thanks to the kindness of a Ranger named Korlian who WON a Random for HIS DR, I was able to purchase it off him for a straight 1500pp...<BR>
I've SINCE bumped into the &quot;greedy&quot; owners and they STILL haven't got what they want so I feel a little sense of &quot;validation&quot;...<BR>
<BR>
And to Bugaar up there...<BR>
It seems a little petty to be gloating that you got a DR for free, and that you're ONLY level 15, but guess what...? That's not REALLY a DR you've got...  What you're holding is, basically, a BIBS until you reach level 30...   and TRUST ME, you'll be doing a LOT of hair-pulling with your char BEFORE that sword becomes useful to you...<BR>
